This project involved developing an object detection system using the PASCAL VOC 2007 dataset , focusing on balancing model accuracy with hardware efficiency. We evaluated 20 distinct object categories and navigated significant computational constraints to optimize performance.

What We Accomplished: 
  Model Implementation: Evaluated SSD MobileNet V2 for efficiency and Faster R-CNN for higher accuracy, though the latter faced resource limitations.  
  Data Engineering: Addressed class imbalances and potential data corruption through a pipeline of data validation, cleansing, and augmentation.  
  Performance Optimization: Managed memory and runtime issues by using reduced batch sizes, model pruning, and early stopping.  
  Advanced Refinement: Integrated Transfer Learning from the COCO dataset to speed up convergence and explored Ensemble Methods to reduce prediction errors.  
  Efficiency Improvements: Researched Model Quantization to minimize file size and enhance real-time inference speeds. 
